The paper deals with the problem of approximating the Kolmogorov-Chaitin complexity of short strings using a numerical approach based on algorithmic probability. This involves analyzing the output frequency distributions of small Turing machines, which is a topic that falls under the purview of information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given that the paper focuses on theoretical computer science and algorithmic analysis, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates.
